data.title: Pinellas County
data.meta_description: A Public Policy of Open Government The Florida Constitution and Florida Statutes §119 and §286 safeguard every Floridian’s right to access government...
data.text:
Please Note: Airport, Building Services, Code Enforcement, Contractor Licensing Department, Development Review Services, Emergency Management, Visit St. Pete/Clearwater, and Workforce Relations are using a new public records system to submit public records requests and track their progress.

Use the Public Records Request form to request records from any of the government offices in the list below.

Animal Services

County Administration

County Attorney

Human Resources

Human Services

Office of Human Rights

Medical Examiner Records: Call (727) 582-6800 and ask to speak with the Records Custodian.

Pinellas County Sheriff’s Office records (email link)

Supervisor of Elections Records

Enter your email address to stay updated on the latest county news, events and opportunities.

Email Address

Phone

This field is for validation purposes and should be left unchanged.

Under Florida law, e-mail addresses are public records. If you do not want your e-mail address released in response to a public records request, do not send electronic mail to this entity. Instead, contact this office by phone or in writing.
